Date: Fri, 20 Jun 2025 14:02:55 +0530
Subject: [PATCH 1/6] UPSTREAM: DP: wifi: ath12k: Segregate Rx and Tx monitor
 processing API's

Currently, a common ring processing API is used for both Rx
and Tx monitor processing by passing the monitor mode (Rx or Tx)
as an argument.

With the Unified Driver framework, Rx monitor supports two
different architectural models, each employing a distinct mechanism
for ring processing. Since Rx and Tx use different rings and
processing mechanisms, segregating Rx and Tx monitor processing.

Patch-dependency:
	0403-0002-UPSTREAM-DP-wifi-ath12k-Refactor-monitor-hal-specifi.patch

Signed-off-by: Sushant Butta <sbutta@qti.qualcomm.com>
